Kidnapping of a union president representing medical doctors is the latest crackdown by the government against its critics. Unidentified men suspected to be state security operatives on Saturday night abducted Peter Magombeyi, leader of the Hospital Doctors Association. READ: MBEKI HAILS MUGABE AN AFRICAN HERO The incident happened before the International Day of Democracy, celebrated every year on 15 September. Magombeyi’s abduction is seen as a ploy by authorities to intimidate angry doctors against staging a protest against poor working conditions. READ: PLEASE ACCEPT OUR APOLOGY, FELLOW AFRICANS The Zimbabwe Lawyers for Human Rights said the kidnapping came in the wake of abductions of human rights doctors. The lawyers said the doctors were tortured and left for dead. – CAJ NEWS